      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRON LEGACY (2) quickly gets to 2400m, but the last run at Stawell, when he got home strongly for third after racing a long way back, suggested he will lap up this trip. He looks to have more upside than most. Similar story with RAINEY (9), who had one more start and also had the benefit of a run over 2600m, when beaten in a three-way photo, and that could prove telling. BAUDIN (7) is the one who brings the best last-start performance, a three-length 7th in the G3 SA Fillies Classic, but she was pretty poor the start prior, so it'd be good to see her do it again. UNTETHERED SOUL (10) has been far from disgraced in any of her starts to date and might be ready for a peak performance out to this trip for the first time, being a daughter of Soul Patch. SPICY APPLE (6) ran the best race of his career last start and looks ready for this trip now.",
